        "subject": "LU-8299 clio: correct arithmetic in cl_index",
        "message": "LU-8299 clio: correct arithmetic in cl_index\n\ncl_index uses a right shift for division, but takes an\nsigned argument (type loff_t).  If the argument is ever\nnegative, a right shift doesn't do division.\n\nMake cl_index take pgoff_t as its argument instead.\nThis is an unsigned type of the same size (and it's what it\nreturns anyway).\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ifa6d0f8809e4c0818f32f0eec81709ae5af599e0\n"
      },
